03/03/2011
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Police announced on Wednesday (March 2nd) the arrest of Ivo Menzalin, suspected of war crimes against civilians committed in 1992 in Croatia. 
Menzalin, 58, was detained at the Podgorica airport after arriving from Belgrade. 
He was allegedly involved in the torture and inhuman treatment of prisoners of war and civilians when he was a member of the Yugoslav National Army. 
(Tanjug, Pcnen, RTCG - 02/03/11)
